7:
I'm glad we made it back from the
island, but...
10:
Crap, I totally lost track of time! The
show's about to start!
14:
Albert! Are you listening to me? Let's
go!
18:
I thought she was going to say Alk's
name... My heart just about leapt
into my throat...
21: This is ridiculous... I can't... I'm not...
25: There is no way I'm in l-love...
29:
Besides, my feelings shouldn't
matter for what I have to do...
33:
Hello, Shywe. Did you sleep well
yesterday? I'm sure you must still be
tired from your ordeal—
44:
Why would you run away the
moment you saw me? Are you
trying to cause a scene?!
49:
L-listen, it's because you were
looking at me weirdly first!
53:
I have n-no idea what you're talking
about. I'm acting completely normal!
56:
Which is absolutely, definitely,
because I'm NOT in love with you!
64:
A-anyway, nothing has changed
between us, so you should take care
to act normal as well—
74: The sprites just spoke to me...
84: It was... more like a request.
93:
N-no, it's honestly not something
difficult. I just...
96:
I can't help but feel cautious after
hearing the voice of the Devourer of
Stars back on the island...
101:
I guess a little bit of caution is
warranted after everything that
happened.
104:
Now that I think about it, what I
heard back then felt distinctly odd...
106:
But the voices from a moment ago
were familiar. It must have been the
sprites who spoke.
110:
Still, there's always a chance you've
been deceived.
114: We'll go with you, just in case.
119:
Weren't you in the middle of running
away, pal?
123:
That was before this came up. I'm
not about to let her charge into
potential danger alone.
136:
This is an undeveloped area, so
there might be monsters around. Be
on guard, everyone—
144:
I have to make up for how little I
contributed while we were stranded.
148:
Eh, don't be too hard on yourself.
There were some fun moments.
156:
Uh, I mean, not at your expense, of
course! I just—
161: I'm not mad! I only wonder...
164:
Is it truly all right for us to think back
fondly of our time there?
168:
Well, I don't know about you, but I
thought it was pretty fun to get
some survival experience in.
170:
Even if we did cause a whole bunch
of stress for everyone else.
174:
No one says you can't have fun
while also struggling for your life
and giving the rest of us a scare.
188: Is this... some sort of burial marker?
193:
I believe it's an altar made from
whatever the people here had on
hand... Or what's left of one, at least.
197:
I wonder if the locals or construction
workers are responsible for building
it.
201:
Don't tell me you got called here to
fix this thing up.
205: I realize it might not look like much...
208:
But the sprites seem happy that
we're here to take care of it.
211:
Guess that means we better do a
bang-up job with our repairs.
221:
How's this look? It's kind of hard to
tell if we did good or not, since the
design's simple...
225:
Judging by the reaction, we've met
their expectations.
229: I hope the sprites forgive me...
234:
I bent my ears to listen to the
Devourer of the Stars back on the
island...
236:
And rejected the voice of the sprites
in turn.
242: They don't appear angry to me.
254:
We just did what anyone else
would've done. Anyway, who's up for
dinner?
259:
I truly wonder if I'm allowed these
experiences...
261:
Troubling others, getting into trouble
myself, and enjoying myself despite
it all...
